%% Diagram: Oblivious DoH — proxy and target separation of identity from query
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant P as Proxy\n(sees client IP only)
    participant T as Target Resolver\n(sees query only)

    Note over C,T: Unlinkability requires proxy and target are not the same operator
    C->>T: HTTPS GET ODoH config (target's HPKE pubkey)
    T-->>C: ObliviousDoHConfigs
    C->>C: HPKE-encrypt DNS query with target pubkey
    C->>P: HTTPS POST encrypted query\n(client IP visible)
    P->>T: Forward encrypted query\n(target sees proxy IP, not client)
    T->>T: HPKE-decrypt, resolve, encrypt response
    T-->>P: Encrypted response
    P-->>C: Encrypted response
    C->>C: HPKE-decrypt response
    Note over P,T: Proxy never sees plaintext query.\nTarget never sees client IP.\nCollusion of both reverses unlinkability.
